text: And upon what things soever any of their carcasses shall fall, it shall be defiled, whether it be a vessel of wood, or a garment, or skins, or haircloths, or anything in which work is done, they shall be dipped in water, and shall be unclean until the evening, and so afterwards shall be cleaned.
